Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

British nationals visiting Slovenia are strongly advised to return to the UK as soon as possible, and should contact their travel operator to make arrangements to do so as soon as possible. If you require additional advice or assistance returning to the UK from Slovenia you should contact the British Embassy at info@british-embassy.si.
Scheduled flights to and from Slovenia are suspended until at least 13 April.
There are currently no commercial routes available to the UK (direct or indirect) from Slovenia. Up-to-date information on commercial flight options from Austria and Croatia and transit options from Slovenia can be found on the British Embassy’s Twitter and Facebook pages.
Neighbouring countries have introduced restrictions on entry from Slovenia see travel advice for Austria, Croatia, Hungary and Italy. Be aware that all requirements can be subject to short notice change or alteration. Check travel advice for any country that you will transit on the way back to the UK.
Passenger trains connections between Slovenia and Austria have been suspended.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
